prompt.user:
Project: {project_name}
Client: {client_name}
Methodology: {methodology}
Service Lines: {service_lines}

Project Type Guidance:
{project_type_guidance}

SOW Summary:
{sow_summary}

Service Line Design Standards:
{standards_context}

HLD Context (align business logic with component responsibilities defined in HLD):
{hld_context}

Generated Requirements Context:
{requirements_context}

REMINDERS:
- SLA formula must use CreatedDate + priority hours → breach detection. NOT (age/2)*100.
- State machine appears ONCE — not once per domain section.
- Escalation ≠ SLA — escalation is the response AFTER breach, not the breach condition itself.
- Assignment algorithm must specify HOW an agent is selected (queue/round-robin/skill/territory).
- Priority SLA tiers must come from SOW. If not found, state "assumed" and make configurable.

Now generate the Business Logic for {project_name}. All rules from THIS project's SOW and requirements. Do NOT add a "Note:" section. Output ONLY markdown.
